Extension: Cross-version Extension `R5.MeasureReport.group` for use in FHIR R4

Official URL: http://hl7.org/fhir/5.0/StructureDefinition/extension-MeasureReport.group Version: 0.0.1-snapshot-3
Standards status: Trial-use Active as of 2026-02-17 Maturity Level: 0 Computable Name: ExtensionMeasureReport_Group

This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element MeasureReport.group for use in FHIR R4.

Context of Use

    This extension may be used on the following element(s)

    • Element ID: MeasureReport.group

    This extension is allowed for use with FHIR versions R4 to R4 .

Usage info

Usages:

  • Use this Extension: Cross-version Profile for R5.MeasureReport for use in FHIR R4

You can also check for usages in the FHIR IG Statistics

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element MeasureReport.group for use in FHIR R4.

  • linkId: string: The group from the Measure that corresponds to this group in the MeasureReport resource.
  • code: CodeableConcept: The meaning of the population group as defined in the measure definition.
  • subject: Reference: Optional subject identifying the individual or individuals the report is for.
  • linkId: string: The population from the Measure that corresponds to this population in the MeasureReport resource.
  • code: CodeableConcept: The type of the population.
  • count: integer: The number of members of the population.
  • subjectResults: Reference: This element refers to a List of individual level MeasureReport resources, one for each subject in this population.
  • subjectReport: Reference: A reference to an individual level MeasureReport resource for a member of the population.
  • subjects: Reference: Optional Group identifying the individuals that make up the population.
  • measureScore: dateTime, CodeableConcept, Period: The measure score for this population group, calculated as appropriate for the measure type and scoring method, and based on the contents of the populations defined in the group.
  • linkId: string: The stratifier from the Measure that corresponds to this stratifier in the MeasureReport resource.
  • code: CodeableConcept: The meaning of this stratifier, as defined in the measure definition.
  • value: boolean, Quantity, Range, Reference: The value for this stratum, expressed as a CodeableConcept. When defining stratifiers on complex values, the value must be rendered such that the value for each stratum within the stratifier is unique.
  • linkId: string: The stratifier component from the Measure that corresponds to this stratifier component in the MeasureReport resource.
  • code: CodeableConcept: The code for the stratum component value.
  • value: boolean, Quantity, Range, Reference: The stratum component value.
  • linkId: string: The population from the Measure that corresponds to this population in the MeasureReport resource.
  • code: CodeableConcept: The type of the population.
  • count: integer: The number of members of the population in this stratum.
  • subjectResults: Reference: This element refers to a List of individual level MeasureReport resources, one for each subject in this population in this stratum.
  • subjectReport: Reference: A reference to an individual level MeasureReport resource for a member of the population.
  • subjects: Reference: Optional Group identifying the individuals that make up the population.
  • measureScore: dateTime, CodeableConcept, Period: The measure score for this stratum, calculated as appropriate for the measure type and scoring method, and based on only the members of this stratum.

Maturity: 0

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element MeasureReport.group for use in FHIR R4.

  • linkId: string: The group from the Measure that corresponds to this group in the MeasureReport resource.
  • code: CodeableConcept: The meaning of the population group as defined in the measure definition.
  • subject: Reference: Optional subject identifying the individual or individuals the report is for.
  • linkId: string: The population from the Measure that corresponds to this population in the MeasureReport resource.
  • code: CodeableConcept: The type of the population.
  • count: integer: The number of members of the population.
  • subjectResults: Reference: This element refers to a List of individual level MeasureReport resources, one for each subject in this population.
  • subjectReport: Reference: A reference to an individual level MeasureReport resource for a member of the population.
  • subjects: Reference: Optional Group identifying the individuals that make up the population.
  • measureScore: dateTime, CodeableConcept, Period: The measure score for this population group, calculated as appropriate for the measure type and scoring method, and based on the contents of the populations defined in the group.
  • linkId: string: The stratifier from the Measure that corresponds to this stratifier in the MeasureReport resource.
  • code: CodeableConcept: The meaning of this stratifier, as defined in the measure definition.
  • value: boolean, Quantity, Range, Reference: The value for this stratum, expressed as a CodeableConcept. When defining stratifiers on complex values, the value must be rendered such that the value for each stratum within the stratifier is unique.
  • linkId: string: The stratifier component from the Measure that corresponds to this stratifier component in the MeasureReport resource.
  • code: CodeableConcept: The code for the stratum component value.
  • value: boolean, Quantity, Range, Reference: The stratum component value.
  • linkId: string: The population from the Measure that corresponds to this population in the MeasureReport resource.
  • code: CodeableConcept: The type of the population.
  • count: integer: The number of members of the population in this stratum.
  • subjectResults: Reference: This element refers to a List of individual level MeasureReport resources, one for each subject in this population in this stratum.
  • subjectReport: Reference: A reference to an individual level MeasureReport resource for a member of the population.
  • subjects: Reference: Optional Group identifying the individuals that make up the population.
  • measureScore: dateTime, CodeableConcept, Period: The measure score for this stratum, calculated as appropriate for the measure type and scoring method, and based on only the members of this stratum.

Maturity: 0

 

Other representations of profile: CSV, Excel, Schematron
